about.summary: The DoseFinding package provides functions for the design and analysis of dose-finding experiments (with focus on pharmaceutical Phase II clinical trials). It provides functions for: multiple contrast tests, fitting non-linear dose-response models (using Bayesian and non-Bayesian estimation), calculating optimal designs and an implementation of the MCPMod methodology.

name: r-dosefinding
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.9-16' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-dosefinding
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  fn: DoseFinding_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/DoseFinding_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/DoseFinding/DoseFinding_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 3f211e022d25bcdeb4532743c293fc460ccb46456f62614daf2e56e268499959

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1002
  skip: true  # [win32]
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{posix}}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{posix}}make
    - {{posix}}sed               # [win]
    - {{posix}}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-lattice
    - r-mvtnorm
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{native}}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-lattice
    - r-mvtnorm

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('DoseFinding')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('DoseFinding')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=DoseFinding
  license: GPL-3
  summary: 'The DoseFinding package provides functions for the design and analysis of dose-finding
    experiments (with focus on pharmaceutical Phase II clinical trials). It provides
    functions for: multiple contrast tests, fitting non-linear dose-response models
    (using Bayesian and non-Bayesian estimation), calculating optimal designs and an
    implementation of the MCPMod methodology.'
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - johanneskoester
    - bgruening
    - daler
    - jdblischak
    - cbrueffer
    - dbast
